==Old English==
===Etymology===
From an Indo-European base ''*kelb-, *kelp-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[helpa]] (Frisian [[helpe]]), Old High German [[helfan]] (German [[helfen]]), Old Saxon ''helpan'' (Dutch [[helpen]]), Old Norse [[hjalpa]] (Swedish [[hjälpa]]), Gothic [[𐌷𐌹𐌻𐍀𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'helpan/

===Verb===
'''helpan''' (class III strong: '''hilfþ''' ‘he helps’; '''healp''' ‘he helped’; '''hulpon''' ‘they helped’; '''ġeholpen''' past participle)
# to [[help]]

